                  Nguyen Dai Nam added a comment - 19/Sep/17 1:50 PM

                  Tran Ha Van-san,

                  Have you check with all kind of symbol (C, Assembly, Variadic, RTOS symbol is supported or not)?

                  The spec. is Stack Analysis only support C function as GCC compiler only supports to output stack size of C/C++ function.
                  Stack size of Assembly function is not available and I'm not sure how to create Variadic and RTOS function with GCC. But even if these function are created, Stack Analysis will judge it as C function.

                  Have you check some source code with complicated relation: a->b > c> a (recursive).

                  Yes, it is checked with attached projects.
                  I also added a test case for the case that a function calls other function many time (TC 52) as I saw problem with that case.

                  2. Please confirm the RZ in case stack file is available.

                  RZ is non-supported project, import stack file job will not run so the existence of stack file is not matter.
